CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 15, 1966, pg. 13A reads: "First Dance - Lovely "Queen" Myra Campbell gives the first dance to John Baker who served as master of ceremonies at the Rainbow Cotillion given by the Civic League of Washington, Pa., in the Ballroom of the George Washington Hotel."
TitMainTitle: "Queen" Myra Campbell dancing with John Baker in George Washington Hotel for Rainbow Cotillion, Washington, Pennsylvania
